1
00:00:04,537 --> 00:00:08,308
<i>Your son shoplifted from my store.</i>

2
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:08,975
<i>What?</i>

3
00:00:09,542 --> 00:00:12,312
<i>That is, if you show me your sincerity.</i>

4
00:00:12,379 --> 00:00:14,714
We shouldn't let him manipulate us
any further.

5
00:00:15,281 --> 00:00:16,850
What is he demanding?

6
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:18,618
<i>Long time no see, Junichi.</i>

7
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:19,786
Junichi?

8
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:23,256
<i>You appeared before him as a detective.</i>

9
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:25,892
Sorry for making you worry.

10
00:00:26,459 --> 00:00:27,127
It's okay.

11
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:30,063
The four people involved in the incident
23 years ago

12
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:32,932
<i>reunited because Sakuma was murdered.</i>

13
00:00:32,999 --> 00:00:35,402
Let's open the time capsule.

14
00:00:35,969 --> 00:00:40,040
This will be a secret between
just the four of us.

15
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:46,146
It's gone.

16
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:50,316
One of us here opened the time capsule
and took out that gun.

17
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:51,785
Give me time. I'll tell the truth.

18
00:00:51,851 --> 00:00:53,019
Why can't you tell me now?

19
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:55,488
I can, but Makiko…

20
00:00:55,555 --> 00:00:59,225
Ms. Makiko Iwamoto is clearly lying.

21
00:00:59,292 --> 00:01:01,795
I went because you suggested it.

22
00:01:01,861 --> 00:01:02,796
Why?

23
00:01:03,363 --> 00:01:04,631
I don't know why.

24
00:01:04,697 --> 00:01:08,968
I remember seeing someone walking around
the school grounds during my evening walk.

25
00:01:09,035 --> 00:01:10,937
It was a black SUV
with a Shinagawa license plate.

26
00:01:11,504 --> 00:01:14,274
<i>Is it because they used to be married?</i>

27
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:18,044
<i>It's very interesting</i>
<i>how perfectly their alibis</i>

28
00:01:19,612 --> 00:01:21,281
<i>line up with each other.</i>

29
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:28,988
On January 18th, just after 9:00 a.m.,

30
00:01:29,055 --> 00:01:31,057
the body of Hideyuki Sakuma, the manager

31
00:01:31,124 --> 00:01:33,326
of Smile Sakuma Mitsuba Minami branch,
was discovered.

32
00:01:33,393 --> 00:01:34,427
<i>The murder weapon was a gun.</i>

33
00:01:34,494 --> 00:01:38,131
The estimated time of death is just before
10:00 p.m. the previous day, Saturday.

34
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:42,268
There are only reports of hearing gunshots
and no eyewitness accounts.

35
00:01:42,836 --> 00:01:44,404
There are no clues to the culprit,

36
00:01:44,471 --> 00:01:46,606
and the murder weapon, the gun,
has not been found.

37
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:47,507
WEAPON - GUN
GUN THAT BELONGED TO OFFICER KIYOHARA

38
00:01:47,574 --> 00:01:50,009
The murder weapon is a gun
that belonged to Officer Kazuo Kiyohara,

39
00:01:50,076 --> 00:01:54,581
who was shot and killed by the perpetrator
of the Yamato Trust Bank

40
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:57,050
<i>armored car robbery 23 years ago.</i>

41
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:00,420
It's the gun that has been missing
for the past 23 years.

42
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:02,889
We must find the culprit

43
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,191
<i>and recover the gun as soon as possible.</i>

44
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:08,061
As for the fact

45
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:11,131
that a police officer's gun was used
as the murder weapon,

46
00:02:11,197 --> 00:02:15,268
the prefectural police's senior officials
are still carefully discussing the matter,

47
00:02:15,335 --> 00:02:17,837
including whether or not
to disclose it to the media.

48
00:02:18,338 --> 00:02:20,140
No conclusion has been reached yet.

49
00:02:20,707 --> 00:02:24,644
Please ensure that this information
is kept confidential.

50
00:02:24,711 --> 00:02:25,745
Yes, sir.

51
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:32,485
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

52
00:02:46,966 --> 00:02:51,037
We have yet to determine the whereabouts
of the victim on the day of the incident.

53
00:02:51,871 --> 00:02:52,839
Sir.

54
00:02:53,773 --> 00:02:55,842
I talked to the employee
at the pachinko parlor

55
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:58,244
but couldn't get any useful information.

56
00:02:58,878 --> 00:03:00,547
Anyone else find any leads?

57
00:03:00,613 --> 00:03:01,447
Yes, sir.

58
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:05,552
Makiko Iwamoto visited Smile Sakuma
the day before the incident,

59
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:08,888
so she was questioned as a witness,
but we have since found out that

60
00:03:08,955 --> 00:03:10,490
she lied in her testimony.

61
00:03:10,557 --> 00:03:11,791
What?

62
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:13,159
On that day, Ms. Iwamoto

63
00:03:13,226 --> 00:03:16,629
went to pick up her sixth-grade son
after he had been caught shoplifting.

64
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:19,265
In exchange for keeping
the shoplifting incident a secret…

65
00:03:19,332 --> 00:03:21,067
You're saying that I have an accomplice?

66
00:03:21,134 --> 00:03:22,202
<i>That night, at 11:00 p.m.,</i>

67
00:03:22,268 --> 00:03:24,904
<i>Ms. Makiko Iwamoto and her ex-husband,</i>
<i>Mr. Keisuke Kiyohara,</i>

68
00:03:24,971 --> 00:03:26,973
went to hand over the 300,000 yen.

69
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:31,344
What were their alibis
on the day of the incident?

70
00:03:32,345 --> 00:03:36,216
Yes, sir. The two were at a restaurant
in the city at 8:00 p.m.

71
00:03:36,282 --> 00:03:40,253
After 8:30 p.m., Ms. Makiko Iwamoto
went to Ma Saison hair salon,

72
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,755
and Mr. Keisuke Kiyohara went to a hotel.

73
00:03:42,822 --> 00:03:45,091
<i>They met again at the restaurant</i>
<i>at 10:30 p.m.</i>

74
00:03:45,592 --> 00:03:48,494
<i>It’s been confirmed that Mr. Kiyohara</i>
<i>did indeed go to the hotel.</i>

75
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:52,131
<i>We have yet to confirm that Ms. Iwamoto</i>
<i>was indeed at the hair salon.</i>

76
00:03:53,499 --> 00:03:54,601
Excuse me.

77
00:03:55,201 --> 00:03:56,402
Has the alibi

78
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:59,872
of the victim's younger brother,
Mr. Naoto Sakuma, been verified?

79
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:01,908
Well? Has it?

80
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:03,409
Yes, sir.

81
00:04:04,944 --> 00:04:07,981
Mr. Naoto Sakuma
returned from Korea on a flight

82
00:04:08,047 --> 00:04:11,951
arriving at Haneda Airport at 8:55 p.m.
He traveled home by car,

83
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:14,487
<i>and due to heavy traffic,</i>
<i>he arrived home shortly before 11:00 p.m.</i>

84
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:18,925
The 8:55 p.m. arrival time at Haneda
has been confirmed with the airline.

85
00:04:18,992 --> 00:04:22,595
His mother has corroborated
that he arrived home before 11:00 p.m.

86
00:04:24,797 --> 00:04:25,632
That's all.

87
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,801
Verify the alibis of Iwamoto and Kiyohara

88
00:04:28,868 --> 00:04:32,105
and re-examine all witness accounts
from the surrounding area. Adjourned.

89
00:04:32,171 --> 00:04:33,206
Yes, sir.

90
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:39,679
- You overslept?
- Sorry.

91
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:46,085
Or are you
investigating something on your own?

92
00:04:46,152 --> 00:04:47,086
No.

93
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:50,456
We're buddy detectives, right?

94
00:04:53,059 --> 00:04:54,494
I can't believe I said "buddy."

95
00:04:58,097 --> 00:04:58,931
I'm sorry.

96
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:00,900
Yes, we're buddies.

97
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,168
We're buddies.

98
00:05:20,253 --> 00:05:22,689
The entrance that will be built
around here

99
00:05:22,755 --> 00:05:25,692
will be made with wood
from trees in Mitsuba City.

100
00:05:26,626 --> 00:05:28,227
We hope to create a shopping mall

101
00:05:28,928 --> 00:05:31,764
that exudes warmth,
and fosters a sense of community,

102
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:35,535
so that everyone
will want to visit every day.

103
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:39,372
Don't you think you should act
a little more like a company president?

104
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:41,441
How does a president act?

105
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,976
I guess they’re usually
confident and sharp.

106
00:05:44,477 --> 00:05:46,579
But I’m not even the president.

107
00:05:46,646 --> 00:05:49,749
You’re the managing director,
but you’re the next president.

108
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:51,784
That’s true, but…

109
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,990
Speaking of which, you used to get
a lot of arranged marriage proposals.

110
00:05:58,057 --> 00:06:01,794
To daughters of local company owners
or the granddaughters of chairmen.

111
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:04,497
I haven't gotten any recently.

112
00:06:05,064 --> 00:06:07,700
Maki told me to show her the photo
next time it happens.

113
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:10,903
We want you to find
a good person to be with.

114
00:06:13,306 --> 00:06:15,942
This is no time
for such carefree conversation.

115
00:06:16,576 --> 00:06:18,878
We’re doing it
because it’s not the right time.

116
00:06:19,979 --> 00:06:21,013
You're right.

117
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:23,649
Oh.

118
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:24,550
What is it?

119
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:27,487
Mom has been wanting
to invite everyone over

120
00:06:28,087 --> 00:06:31,290
for some hand-rolled sushi and madeleines,
just like the old days.

121
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,259
Hand-rolled sushi?

122
00:06:33,326 --> 00:06:34,961
Junichi especially loved those.

123
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:35,995
Yeah.

124
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,064
Bye.

125
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:39,132
Bye.

126
00:06:44,003 --> 00:06:44,837
Hello?

127
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:48,541
Keisuke? Are you in Tokyo right now?

128
00:06:49,275 --> 00:06:50,576
<i>No, I’m in Mitsuba.</i>

129
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,148
Then how about we have a match?

130
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:57,650
A match?

131
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:09,562
How many years has it been?
Fifteen? Sixteen?

132
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:10,563
You've got good footwork.

133
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,331
I guess it’s muscle memory.

134
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,603
You've still got it. You’ll be fine.

135
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:19,105
Although I’ll be no match for you.

136
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:21,274
It's okay. I’ll go easy on you.

137
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:22,575
Yes, please.

138
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:27,513
We haven’t had a match since that day.

139
00:07:28,514 --> 00:07:29,582
When we were in sixth grade.

140
00:07:30,683 --> 00:07:31,951
<i>Red, Tobina.</i>

141
00:07:32,018 --> 00:07:33,085
Ready.

142
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:36,222
- White, Kiyohara.
- Ready.

143
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:37,690
IROHADAI
KIYOHARA

144
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,826
- Take position.
- Maki,

145
00:07:39,892 --> 00:07:41,093
- who are you cheering on?
- Bow.

146
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:45,832
You’ll just have to cheer
for both of them, huh?

147
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:49,969
I’m going to cheer on the match.

148
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:51,838
Cheer on the match?

149
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:55,708
Let's cheer them on so that it will be
a memorable match

150
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,510
for everyone.

151
00:07:57,577 --> 00:07:58,778
Yeah.

152
00:07:58,845 --> 00:08:00,413
Good idea, Maki.

153
00:08:10,122 --> 00:08:10,990
Begin.

154
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:40,186
You can do it.

155
00:08:41,921 --> 00:08:43,022
Winner.

156
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:49,962
Keisuke.

157
00:08:50,029 --> 00:08:51,797
Keisuke!

158
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,066
- You were strong too.
- Good job.

159
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:54,967
Good job.

160
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,227
Keisuke, you're the one who opened

161
00:09:23,829 --> 00:09:24,897
the time capsule, right?

162
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:28,568
What?

163
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:33,239
On Friday night,
the day before the incident,

164
00:09:34,974 --> 00:09:37,510
your car was spotted
near the abandoned school.

165
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:40,680
- Someone also saw a man walking through--
- Wait, hold on!

166
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:42,615
- Did you take out the gun?
- No, it wasn’t me.

167
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:45,518
Then why were you there?

168
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,031
It’s true

169
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,435
that I went there to open
the time capsule.

170
00:10:04,403 --> 00:10:06,172
But the gun was already gone.

171
00:10:07,573 --> 00:10:08,641
What?

172
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:12,044
I opened the time capsule,
but there was no gun inside.

173
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:15,748
- Are you serious?
- I’m not lying.

174
00:10:17,917 --> 00:10:19,819
Why did you dig up the time capsule?

175
00:10:21,253 --> 00:10:25,024
I was thinking of taking it with me for
self-defense when I went to see Sakuma.

176
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:30,630
You might not believe it,
but the gun was already gone.

177
00:10:30,696 --> 00:10:33,532
I even have an alibi during the time
Sakuma was killed.

178
00:10:33,599 --> 00:10:35,835
I didn't use the gun,
or take it from the time capsule.

179
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:41,173
What if the person who took the gun
and the person who used it

180
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:43,876
were two different people?

181
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:46,078
What?

182
00:10:50,282 --> 00:10:51,984
Makiko's alibi has not been proven.

183
00:10:54,453 --> 00:10:56,555
Are you trying to say that I took the gun,

184
00:10:56,622 --> 00:10:58,724
and then Makiko used it?

185
00:10:59,792 --> 00:11:01,627
There's no way I'd let Makiko do that.

186
00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:04,463
- I don’t think that you would either!
- Then what is it?

187
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,068
Either way, the gun was gone.

188
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:13,172
I haven't told anyone that I went
to dig it up. Not even Makiko.

189
00:11:16,542 --> 00:11:17,643
So?

190
00:11:18,644 --> 00:11:20,680
The time capsule was opened two times.

191
00:11:29,655 --> 00:11:32,925
That means someone took the gun
out of that time capsule years ago,

192
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,261
and kept it hidden?

193
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:36,829
That’s the only possible answer.

194
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,166
If you’re telling the truth,

195
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:43,436
then it would have to be either
Makiko or Naoto.

196
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:49,909
What if

197
00:11:50,643 --> 00:11:51,744
it’s Naoto?

198
00:11:54,613 --> 00:11:57,349
If Naoto had dug up that gun
a few years ago…

199
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:00,753
Let’s say

200
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:04,156
that he knew he couldn't possibly
beat his brother in a physical fight.

201
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:06,959
So he wanted to have a powerful weapon
and opened the time capsule.

202
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:09,829
Even if he had taken the gun
and kept it hidden all this time,

203
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:13,699
do you really think he would use it
because he hated his brother?

204
00:12:18,003 --> 00:12:19,638
Of all things, it was your pops' gun.

205
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:24,076
He's not that kind of guy.

206
00:12:24,777 --> 00:12:26,312
He could never kill anyone.

207
00:12:26,378 --> 00:12:27,646
Makiko wouldn’t either.

208
00:12:27,713 --> 00:12:28,748
Yeah.

209
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:33,819
I don’t think she’d dig up
the time capsule either.

210
00:12:41,627 --> 00:12:44,497
KOTONO

211
00:12:44,997 --> 00:12:45,965
I have to take this.

212
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:03,616
Don’t you have any friends
to play catch with?

213
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:05,217
No.

214
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:07,520
I see.

215
00:13:08,521 --> 00:13:09,855
Maybe I'll play with you.

216
00:13:11,357 --> 00:13:12,191
Oh, come on.

217
00:13:12,258 --> 00:13:15,461
You don't have to look so disgusted
by that idea.

218
00:13:19,398 --> 00:13:21,433
Let’s eat. Go wash your hands.

219
00:13:23,402 --> 00:13:24,403
Okay.

220
00:13:31,277 --> 00:13:32,378
<i>Okay.</i>

221
00:13:33,612 --> 00:13:35,047
Take it easy and rest.

222
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:37,416
Bye.

223
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,662
That was a call from my wife.

224
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:53,532
I remarried.

225
00:13:56,569 --> 00:13:57,503
When?

226
00:13:58,037 --> 00:13:59,271
A year ago.

227
00:14:00,539 --> 00:14:01,941
She’s pregnant.

228
00:14:02,975 --> 00:14:04,210
Does Makiko know?

229
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:05,978
No.

230
00:14:07,479 --> 00:14:10,850
She doesn’t know about the marriage
or the kid.

231
00:14:12,585 --> 00:14:15,921
I was going to tell her after Masaki's
exams, but then the incident happened,

232
00:14:16,422 --> 00:14:17,590
so she doesn't know yet.

233
00:14:21,894 --> 00:14:23,395
Please don’t tell Makiko about it.

234
00:14:23,963 --> 00:14:26,098
Of course. It's not my place to say.

235
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,200
Yeah, you're right.

236
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:34,206
Married twice with two kids, huh?

237
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:37,776
I guess I prefer to be married.

238
00:14:39,411 --> 00:14:40,479
But you got divorced.

239
00:14:41,747 --> 00:14:43,382
You make no sense.

240
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:45,584
I wasn’t the right fit
as Makiko’s husband, that’s all.

241
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:50,055
Hey,

242
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:53,959
what do you think Makiko will say
when I tell her I remarried?

243
00:14:56,161 --> 00:14:58,030
Makiko isn’t the only one
who'd have an opinion.

244
00:14:58,797 --> 00:15:00,766
- You mean Naoto?
- Yeah.

245
00:15:02,001 --> 00:15:03,936
- He’ll probably get mad.
- For sure.

246
00:15:05,838 --> 00:15:07,773
I haven't told my wife about the incident.

247
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:10,643
I'm hiding things
from both her and Makiko.

248
00:15:10,709 --> 00:15:12,111
It's so exhausting.

249
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:15,214
You’ve always been
tiptoeing around other people.

250
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,650
I don’t want anyone to not like me.

251
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:25,758
I know that.

252
00:15:25,824 --> 00:15:27,860
How annoying.

253
00:15:37,369 --> 00:15:38,437
Don’t you have to go?

254
00:15:39,905 --> 00:15:41,073
Where are you headed now?

255
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:44,643
I’m going back to the station.

256
00:15:46,912 --> 00:15:47,813
Then let’s go.

257
00:15:50,582 --> 00:15:51,417
Let’s go.

258
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:55,788
Here.

259
00:15:55,854 --> 00:15:56,822
Thanks.

260
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:01,026
What a hassle.

261
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:05,030
- So immature.
- Let's go.

262
00:16:09,435 --> 00:16:11,337
- Hope your wife is okay.
- Thanks.

263
00:16:13,605 --> 00:16:14,740
Hey.

264
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:16,442
Yeah?

265
00:16:17,409 --> 00:16:19,912
What did you think when you met Makiko
for the first time in 23 years?

266
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:23,515
What?

267
00:16:27,619 --> 00:16:28,654
Never mind. Let's go.

268
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:43,068
MAKIKO IWAMOTO

269
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:44,970
<i>Please give me a call.</i>

270
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:55,781
JUNICHI

271
00:16:57,950 --> 00:16:58,784
Junichi?

272
00:16:59,385 --> 00:17:00,285
Yeah.

273
00:17:01,086 --> 00:17:01,987
What’s up?

274
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,125
<i>Listen,</i>

275
00:17:07,793 --> 00:17:11,764
<i>I don't know if I should be saying this</i>
<i>given our current situation, but…</i>

276
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:15,267
Then

277
00:17:16,135 --> 00:17:17,069
maybe you shouldn’t.

278
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:19,805
I guess so, huh?

279
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,574
I figured as much.

280
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:25,577
<i>But you’ll say it anyways, right?</i>

281
00:17:26,945 --> 00:17:27,813
Yeah.

282
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,317
What is it?

283
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:36,055
If you have time,

284
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,224
I'd like you to play catch
with Masaki again.

285
00:17:42,194 --> 00:17:45,964
<i>I totally understand if you say no.</i>

286
00:17:46,031 --> 00:17:46,932
Sure.

287
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:48,600
<i>Sure, what?</i>

288
00:17:49,368 --> 00:17:51,036
Sure, I can play catch.

289
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,639
Really? It's not too much for you?

290
00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:55,307
<i>No.</i>

291
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,745
Yay!

292
00:17:59,812 --> 00:18:01,580
Masaki will be so happy.

293
00:18:02,381 --> 00:18:04,116
Oh, if you have time, stay for dinner too.

294
00:18:08,687 --> 00:18:09,555
Okay.

295
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:13,859
<i>I’ll contact you again.</i>

296
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,395
Okay, bye.

297
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:17,863
<i>Bye.</i>

298
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:26,438
It seemed like you were enjoying
that call.

299
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:28,774
You were still here, huh?

300
00:18:30,509 --> 00:18:34,046
I’m reviewing the case from 23 years ago
to make sure nothing was overlooked.

301
00:18:35,481 --> 00:18:36,482
By the way,

302
00:18:37,382 --> 00:18:39,485
what is your alibi, Detective Tobina?

303
00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:40,786
What?

304
00:18:40,853 --> 00:18:42,988
I’m just asking as a formality.

305
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:46,225
Of the people involved
with the incident 23 years ago,

306
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:50,229
I've already asked Ms. Makiko Iwamoto,
Mr. Keisuke Kiyohara,

307
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:52,664
and Mr. Naoto Sakuma about their alibis.

308
00:18:55,601 --> 00:18:59,438
Detective Tobina,
where were you and what were you doing

309
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:02,007
on the night of the incident?

310
00:19:03,342 --> 00:19:05,310
Where were you and what were you doing

311
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,779
on the night of the incident?

312
00:19:14,286 --> 00:19:15,854
Playing mahjong at a mahjong parlor.

313
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,425
I lost horribly.

314
00:19:21,927 --> 00:19:23,762
I see.

315
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:42,214
Excuse me.

316
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:44,616
I'm Tobina from the Mitsuba Police.

317
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,186
Sorry to bother you,
but can I ask you some questions?

318
00:19:47,252 --> 00:19:49,755
MITSUBA POLICE

319
00:19:49,821 --> 00:19:52,658
Oh man, it's so cold.

320
00:19:52,724 --> 00:19:54,960
I'm back.

321
00:19:55,561 --> 00:19:56,528
Ms. Nara.

322
00:19:57,062 --> 00:19:59,131
Ms. Nara, I got the <i>monaka</i> from Kigetsu.

323
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:02,367
And here's your change.

324
00:20:02,434 --> 00:20:05,237
Sorry, there's lots of coins.

325
00:20:05,771 --> 00:20:07,639
Are there any developments regarding <i>that?</i>

326
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:09,675
I'm still investigating.

327
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:12,511
Just to confirm,

328
00:20:12,578 --> 00:20:14,947
you haven't mentioned <i>that</i>
to Detective Tobina, have you?

329
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:16,415
No.

330
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,685
But are you sure about this?

331
00:20:19,751 --> 00:20:20,619
He’s your buddy, right?

332
00:20:20,686 --> 00:20:23,255
Detective Tanaka,
please continue working hard.

333
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:27,326
I'm Nagai.

334
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:31,096
You bloomed so beautifully.

335
00:20:31,597 --> 00:20:32,965
Chief Kosugi!

336
00:20:33,966 --> 00:20:35,634
Do you like <i>monaka?</i>

337
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,136
You conducted research on me, huh?

338
00:20:38,203 --> 00:20:40,138
Guilty as charged.

339
00:20:40,639 --> 00:20:41,974
I love it.

340
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,610
Can we enjoy these in your office?

341
00:20:44,676 --> 00:20:46,678
Of course. Let's go.

342
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:47,646
KIGETSU

343
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:49,181
Chief Kosugi,

344
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:53,318
since when have you worked
here at Mitsuba Police Station?

345
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:57,656
I first worked here 25 years ago,

346
00:20:57,723 --> 00:20:59,524
then moved around to various places,

347
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:03,362
and returned five years ago
as the police chief.

348
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:08,200
The weapon used to murder Sakuma
was the gun of Officer Kazuo Kiyohara,

349
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:10,969
who died in the line of duty 23 years ago.

350
00:21:11,036 --> 00:21:11,903
Yes.

351
00:21:12,404 --> 00:21:15,741
Keisuke Kiyohara,
the son of Officer Kiyohara,

352
00:21:15,807 --> 00:21:19,711
was one of the people questioned
as a witness in the Sakuma murder case.

353
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:24,016
The other people I spoke to are

354
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:26,118
<i>Keisuke Kiyohara's ex-wife,</i>
<i>Makiko Iwamoto,</i>

355
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:29,988
the victim Hideyuki Sakuma's brother,
Naoto Sakuma,

356
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:32,891
and Detective Junichi Tobina,

357
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,559
<i>who was assigned here two months ago.</i>

358
00:21:35,327 --> 00:21:38,230
They were the first to discover
the body of Officer Kazuo Kiyohara

359
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:42,067
when they were all in the sixth grade
of elementary school?

360
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:43,502
Were you aware of that?

361
00:21:44,069 --> 00:21:45,003
Yes.

362
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:51,576
How did you find out, Ms. Nara?

363
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:56,014
I read all the investigation materials
from that time, cover to cover.

364
00:21:56,548 --> 00:21:57,683
I see.

365
00:21:57,749 --> 00:22:01,586
I would like to speak again
with people who were familiar

366
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:03,455
with the situation at that time.

367
00:22:05,724 --> 00:22:09,261
When that incident happened, I was working
in the administration department,

368
00:22:09,795 --> 00:22:13,732
but I was called into action because
a robber and murderer was on the loose.

369
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:17,102
<i>The four of them,</i>
<i>who were still kids at the time,</i>

370
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:20,339
<i>were taken in since they were</i>
<i>the first to discover the bodies,</i>

371
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:23,375
<i>and I was there to see all that unfold.</i>

372
00:22:24,443 --> 00:22:28,513
When Detective Tobina was assigned here
two months ago,

373
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:32,517
you knew that he was one of the boys
from back then?

374
00:22:33,218 --> 00:22:34,086
Yes.

375
00:22:34,653 --> 00:22:37,989
The incident from 23 years ago
and Sakuma's murder

376
00:22:38,623 --> 00:22:40,992
are connected by Officer Kiyohara's gun,

377
00:22:41,059 --> 00:22:43,929
and the four classmates.

378
00:22:44,896 --> 00:22:48,767
I don't know how being the first
to discover the police officer's body

379
00:22:49,668 --> 00:22:54,005
affected the children's lives afterward,

380
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,975
but in Tobina's case,

381
00:22:57,042 --> 00:23:00,946
there's no doubt that he is currently
a very excellent police officer.

382
00:23:01,012 --> 00:23:07,185
Even if his classmate
is involved with Hideyuki Sakuma's murder,

383
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:12,023
Tobina would never allow personal matters
to affect his investigation.

384
00:23:15,594 --> 00:23:18,897
I’m glad I got to hear your input.

385
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:25,704
- I’ll be going now.
- What?

386
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:27,706
You’re not going to eat the <i>monaka?</i>

387
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:32,244
I'm in the mood for something spicy
rather than something sweet.

388
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:33,278
I'll be going now.

389
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:35,347
Then I’ll enjoy these myself.

390
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,115
Please do. Excuse me.

391
00:23:43,555 --> 00:23:45,357
I’ll meet up with you later too.

392
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:47,292
- What?
- Don't sound so disappointed.

393
00:23:48,059 --> 00:23:49,661
- Have fun.
- Bye.

394
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,196
- You forgot your ball!
- What?

395
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:54,699
You can't forget the ball.

396
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:56,368
- Catch.
- You scared me!

397
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:57,302
- Here.
- Thanks.

398
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:59,204
- Bye.
- Bye.

399
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:00,772
- Be careful.
- Yeah.

400
00:24:12,851 --> 00:24:14,252
Let's use this.

401
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:23,462
Thank you. Goodbye.

402
00:24:29,401 --> 00:24:31,436
- Sore muscles?
- Yeah.

403
00:24:32,003 --> 00:24:34,973
Actually, I did kendo yesterday
as part of a work-related activity.

404
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,709
- You can do kendo?
- I did it from elementary to high school.

405
00:24:37,776 --> 00:24:39,811
- Oh really?
- I was pretty strong.

406
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:42,747
My dad taught it in elementary school,

407
00:24:43,248 --> 00:24:45,650
and our team won
a competition in sixth grade.

408
00:24:49,754 --> 00:24:52,557
<i>In the individual competition,</i>
<i>my teammate won first place,</i>

409
00:24:53,058 --> 00:24:54,860
and I came in second.

410
00:24:57,229 --> 00:25:00,165
My dad was the teacher,
so I felt that I had to be the best.

411
00:25:04,536 --> 00:25:05,470
You know,

412
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:10,175
when I was in elementary school, I was
good at sports, academics, everything.

413
00:25:11,109 --> 00:25:16,515
But he always defeated me, when it came to
things that I desperately wanted to win.

414
00:25:17,616 --> 00:25:21,086
Did that person
defeat you in anything aside from kendo?

415
00:25:23,121 --> 00:25:23,955
Yeah…

416
00:25:24,823 --> 00:25:25,991
Sounds good.

417
00:25:26,658 --> 00:25:27,526
Will you guys come too?

418
00:25:28,093 --> 00:25:29,327
Yeah.

419
00:25:34,599 --> 00:25:37,402
But I don’t remember.
Not sure what it was now.

420
00:25:40,605 --> 00:25:41,640
I'll be off now.

421
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:43,275
Bye.

422
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,715
Masaki, hold it like this.

423
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:53,418
Grip the ball like this.

424
00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:56,154
- Like this, got it?
- Okay.

425
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:57,188
Try it.

426
00:25:59,157 --> 00:26:00,892
- Like this?
- Yeah.

427
00:26:00,959 --> 00:26:02,561
- Try throwing it like that.
- Okay.

428
00:26:05,130 --> 00:26:06,298
That was cool.

429
00:26:06,364 --> 00:26:07,332
One more time.

430
00:26:08,733 --> 00:26:09,868
- Okay.
- Good.

431
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:11,436
Like this.

432
00:26:12,637 --> 00:26:14,039
- Like this?
- Good.

433
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:20,946
It's a lot faster now.

434
00:26:21,012 --> 00:26:22,647
Thank you so much.

435
00:26:26,318 --> 00:26:27,852
- Good job.
- That was good.

436
00:26:29,654 --> 00:26:31,656
I'm back.

437
00:26:31,723 --> 00:26:32,958
Thanks.

438
00:26:33,024 --> 00:26:33,925
Masaki, break time.

439
00:26:33,992 --> 00:26:34,826
Okay.

440
00:26:38,663 --> 00:26:39,731
Masaki.

441
00:26:40,865 --> 00:26:41,833
My mom's here.

442
00:26:43,168 --> 00:26:44,235
Hello.

443
00:26:48,707 --> 00:26:49,941
This is Mr. Junichi's girlfriend.

444
00:26:50,942 --> 00:26:52,510
Nice to meet you. I'm Hiromi.

445
00:26:53,478 --> 00:26:55,113
I'm Masaki's mother.

446
00:26:55,647 --> 00:26:57,616
Hiromi happened to have a day off today.

447
00:26:59,017 --> 00:27:02,354
Sorry to make you hang out with Masaki
on your day off.

448
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:03,788
Not at all.

449
00:27:03,855 --> 00:27:05,657
Junichi is having the most fun.

450
00:27:06,691 --> 00:27:07,726
That's true.

451
00:27:09,027 --> 00:27:11,029
Time to switch. I want to play too.

452
00:27:11,563 --> 00:27:12,631
You can do it?

453
00:27:12,697 --> 00:27:15,133
- I'll do it. I'm sure I can.
- Can you really?

454
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,434
- Really?
- Yeah.

455
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:17,402
Ready.

456
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:18,937
Wow.

457
00:27:19,004 --> 00:27:20,205
- I caught it.
- Nice.

458
00:27:20,772 --> 00:27:21,706
I'll throw it now.

459
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:23,642
Junichi…

460
00:27:23,708 --> 00:27:24,976
That's what she calls you, huh?

461
00:27:26,711 --> 00:27:27,612
Yeah. So?

462
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,981
You guys are really far apart, huh?

463
00:27:30,048 --> 00:27:31,249
- In age?
- Yeah.

464
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:32,217
Ten years.

465
00:27:32,717 --> 00:27:34,152
She's so young.

466
00:27:34,886 --> 00:27:36,254
But she's mature for her age.

467
00:27:37,222 --> 00:27:39,491
- Yeah, she's really calm.
- Yeah.

468
00:27:39,557 --> 00:27:41,192
- What does she do for work?
- She's a nurse.

469
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:48,066
Oh, it makes sense now…

470
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:49,567
What do you mean?

471
00:27:50,101 --> 00:27:51,336
You approached her at the hospital?

472
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:53,371
No, she approached me.

473
00:27:53,438 --> 00:27:56,041
- Are you serious?
- Yes, I'm serious.

474
00:27:56,608 --> 00:27:58,643
- The cut is pretty deep.
- Yes.

475
00:27:59,277 --> 00:28:01,312
I was chasing a pick-pocket

476
00:28:01,379 --> 00:28:05,150
and I almost tripped,
so I grabbed on to the guardrail.

477
00:28:05,216 --> 00:28:06,351
Then this happened.

478
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:07,852
Let's stitch it up.

479
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:09,521
- It needs stitching?
- Yes.

480
00:28:09,587 --> 00:28:10,955
- Clean the wound please.
- Yes.

481
00:28:13,258 --> 00:28:15,427
Please place your hand here.

482
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:19,564
It might sting a little.

483
00:28:25,603 --> 00:28:26,604
Mr. Tobina.

484
00:28:27,138 --> 00:28:27,972
Yes?

485
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:31,276
Um…

486
00:28:32,677 --> 00:28:34,446
Can I ask you for advice about something?

487
00:28:52,163 --> 00:28:53,598
Stay away from Hiromi.

488
00:28:54,099 --> 00:28:56,201
- I've done nothing.
- You're following her every night.

489
00:28:56,267 --> 00:28:58,269
No I am not. Leave me alone.

490
00:28:58,336 --> 00:28:59,537
Not so fast.

491
00:28:59,604 --> 00:29:00,605
- Hey.
- Let me go.

492
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:02,207
Hey, hold on.

493
00:29:02,273 --> 00:29:03,274
Don't get carried away.

494
00:29:04,442 --> 00:29:05,376
Hey.

495
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:08,079
- Don't get cocky with me.
- Sorry.

496
00:29:08,146 --> 00:29:09,481
- I'm sorry.
- What'd you say?

497
00:29:09,547 --> 00:29:10,882
I'm sorry. I'll stop.

498
00:29:10,949 --> 00:29:12,917
That's how it began.

499
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:16,454
How long have you guys been going out?

500
00:29:17,889 --> 00:29:18,957
About three years.

501
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:21,159
I see.

502
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:22,761
Yeah.

503
00:29:22,827 --> 00:29:24,696
Two months ago,

504
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:27,832
I was assigned to Mitsuba Police Station,
and Hiromi tagged along.

505
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:30,969
Tagged along?

506
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:34,072
She came to my place
and made herself at home.

507
00:29:35,140 --> 00:29:36,941
You two are living together?

508
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:38,810
Yeah.

509
00:29:44,048 --> 00:29:45,049
Are you going to marry her?

510
00:29:53,892 --> 00:29:54,826
Junichi.

511
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:57,295
Yeah?

512
00:29:57,362 --> 00:29:58,296
Let's switch.

513
00:29:59,097 --> 00:29:59,998
That was fast.

514
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:01,766
I played enough.

515
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:02,834
Okay.

516
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:07,939
- You had fun?
- I did my best. It was fun.

517
00:30:08,006 --> 00:30:08,973
You weren't bad.

518
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,775
Really? Then praise me.

519
00:30:10,842 --> 00:30:11,876
- What?
- Praise me.

520
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:21,786
Nice.

521
00:30:22,353 --> 00:30:23,955
I'm so glad I got to meet you.

522
00:30:24,022 --> 00:30:25,490
Oh, you are?

523
00:30:26,691 --> 00:30:30,094
Since Junichi never talked about
his friends before.

524
00:30:32,463 --> 00:30:35,333
I haven't really seen him play catch
before either.

525
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:38,169
He'll be a great dad.

526
00:30:40,471 --> 00:30:44,676
Oh sorry, don't take that to mean
that I'm rushing you guys into marriage.

527
00:30:44,742 --> 00:30:45,977
No worries.

528
00:30:48,279 --> 00:30:50,181
We never discuss marriage.

529
00:30:51,816 --> 00:30:55,186
Well, you're still only 25, right?

530
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:57,255
Yeah…

531
00:30:57,322 --> 00:31:00,391
But I don't think that's the issue.

532
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:04,362
Sorry, it's complicated.

533
00:31:07,265 --> 00:31:08,666
I just don't think

534
00:31:09,601 --> 00:31:12,937
this relationship will lead to marriage,
that's all.

535
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:16,608
I see.

536
00:31:18,676 --> 00:31:19,844
But

537
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:22,814
it feels great to spend time outside.

538
00:31:24,616 --> 00:31:29,787
It's been a long time
since we went out together like this.

539
00:31:30,421 --> 00:31:31,890
I see.

540
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:36,160
After this,
we're stopping by the supermarket

541
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,631
to make hand-rolled sushi at home.

542
00:31:41,699 --> 00:31:42,967
Is that right?

543
00:31:43,468 --> 00:31:46,104
Junichi suddenly said that he wanted
to eat hand-rolled sushi.

544
00:31:48,139 --> 00:31:49,040
I see.

545
00:31:50,909 --> 00:31:52,977
I'm getting fired up now.

546
00:31:53,044 --> 00:31:54,245
- All right.
- Let's do this.

547
00:32:07,592 --> 00:32:09,260
Wash your hands.

548
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:25,777
Hello?

549
00:32:25,843 --> 00:32:27,879
Hey.

550
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:30,214
I know it's sudden,
but can I see Masaki today?

551
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:31,215
What?

552
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:33,184
<i>I have some time today.</i>

553
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:36,854
Yeah, sure.

554
00:32:37,855 --> 00:32:39,590
<i>Maybe the three of us can go eat out.</i>

555
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:43,828
Come eat at our place.

556
00:32:44,395 --> 00:32:46,064
I already prepared dinner.

557
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:49,233
And it's more relaxing at home.

558
00:32:50,401 --> 00:32:52,170
Okay. Bye.

559
00:33:00,244 --> 00:33:01,312
Hand-rolled sushi?

560
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,414
Why are you laughing?

561
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:07,051
It's just that Naoto and I
were just talking about hand-rolled sushi.

562
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:08,319
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

563
00:33:08,386 --> 00:33:09,687
It was fun back then.

564
00:33:09,754 --> 00:33:12,323
Junichi was always eating
Alaskan pink shrimp.

565
00:33:12,824 --> 00:33:14,525
You have such a good memory.

566
00:33:16,194 --> 00:33:17,996
- Hey Masaki.
- Dad, you’re late.

567
00:33:18,062 --> 00:33:19,998
- Sorry.
- I'm so hungry.

568
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:22,066
What did you do today?

569
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,134
I was playing catch.

570
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:25,103
- With your friend?
- No, Mr. Junichi.

571
00:33:26,437 --> 00:33:27,572
What?

572
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:31,142
Yeah. Junichi played catch with him.

573
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:34,345
Since your dad bought you
a baseball glove,

574
00:33:34,412 --> 00:33:36,214
- but never comes to play with you, right?
- Yeah.

575
00:33:38,116 --> 00:33:39,117
I'm sorry.

576
00:33:40,018 --> 00:33:42,286
I played catch
with Mr. Junichi's girlfriend too.

577
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,255
- Girlfriend?
- Yeah.

578
00:33:44,322 --> 00:33:46,357
Junichi brought his girlfriend.

579
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:48,326
I see.

580
00:33:49,260 --> 00:33:51,662
She was really cute, wasn't she?

581
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:54,866
I guess so.

582
00:33:54,932 --> 00:33:55,933
You guess so?

583
00:33:56,868 --> 00:33:58,870
Apparently, they're living together.

584
00:33:59,904 --> 00:34:00,905
I see.

585
00:34:04,142 --> 00:34:05,676
Okay, let's eat.

586
00:34:07,412 --> 00:34:09,113
Thank you for the food.

587
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:10,248
Thank you.

588
00:34:20,525 --> 00:34:22,226
Do you like it that much?

589
00:34:22,293 --> 00:34:23,194
Yeah.

590
00:34:23,861 --> 00:34:26,431
I love the taste, color, everything.

591
00:34:27,632 --> 00:34:28,666
I see.

592
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,003
What about you?

593
00:34:32,670 --> 00:34:34,038
- Me?
- Yeah.

594
00:34:34,972 --> 00:34:36,941
I like dried seaweed.

595
00:34:37,475 --> 00:34:38,376
Dried seaweed?

596
00:34:40,144 --> 00:34:41,079
That's your favorite?

597
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:44,115
I like it the best.

598
00:34:47,452 --> 00:34:48,519
Dried seaweed, huh?

599
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:50,555
I see.

600
00:34:52,557 --> 00:34:54,992
Why did you decide to take me along?

601
00:34:58,796 --> 00:34:59,664
I wonder why.

602
00:35:01,632 --> 00:35:02,567
Do I need a reason?

603
00:35:04,402 --> 00:35:06,704
I had fun. Thanks for taking me.

604
00:35:35,833 --> 00:35:37,401
Was Masaki sleeping?

605
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:38,302
What?

606
00:35:38,803 --> 00:35:40,671
Yeah. He's fast asleep.

607
00:35:43,207 --> 00:35:44,742
You haven't opened this yet?

608
00:35:45,343 --> 00:35:46,377
Yeah.

609
00:35:46,944 --> 00:35:49,747
I don't drink wine by myself
when I'm at home.

610
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:50,815
You drink beer?

611
00:35:51,582 --> 00:35:52,416
Yeah.

612
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:56,387
Keisuke, do you drink wine by yourself?

613
00:35:57,522 --> 00:35:59,557
No, I don't drink it either.

614
00:36:19,810 --> 00:36:22,480
Whoa! Oh no!

615
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:43,527
It's Naoto.

616
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:48,199
Sorry to come by so late.

617
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:49,467
What's wrong?

618
00:37:49,533 --> 00:37:51,502
- Hey Keisuke.
- Come inside.

619
00:37:52,203 --> 00:37:53,371
Is that all right?

620
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:55,773
Of course. Come in.

621
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:00,177
I'm not here for any particular reason.

622
00:38:00,244 --> 00:38:02,513
I was passing by and saw Keisuke's car.

623
00:38:03,347 --> 00:38:04,815
You feel anxious being alone, right?

624
00:38:05,916 --> 00:38:09,587
Not that gathering together
will change anything.

625
00:38:10,721 --> 00:38:12,523
Should we call Junichi too?

626
00:38:14,458 --> 00:38:17,895
Junichi has a girlfriend he's living with.

627
00:38:18,863 --> 00:38:20,531
- They're living together?
- Yeah.

628
00:38:22,066 --> 00:38:24,001
- Did you know about this?
- No. I just found out.

629
00:38:24,068 --> 00:38:25,703
I just found out today as well.

630
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:30,241
This happened before, didn't it?

631
00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:32,610
You felt that you were left out
and started sulking.

632
00:38:33,411 --> 00:38:34,412
I remember that.

633
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:36,981
- You guys didn't leave me out on purpose?
- Of course not!

634
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:38,049
You know, Naoto,

635
00:38:38,115 --> 00:38:42,286
you probably forgot what you heard,
and ended up thinking no one told you.

636
00:38:42,353 --> 00:38:44,155
You're so mean, Maki.

637
00:38:45,022 --> 00:38:47,291
I'll message Junichi just in case.

638
00:38:47,792 --> 00:38:49,327
- You don't have to.
- You don't have to.

639
00:38:55,232 --> 00:38:56,200
Here.

640
00:38:59,837 --> 00:39:00,905
I'm going out for a bit.

641
00:39:02,206 --> 00:39:03,407
Mahjong?

642
00:39:05,743 --> 00:39:07,178
- Have fun.
- Okay.

643
00:39:12,983 --> 00:39:16,821
NAOTO SAKUMA

644
00:39:16,887 --> 00:39:18,456
<i>I'm at Maki's house right now.</i>

645
00:39:18,956 --> 00:39:20,925
<i>Keisuke is here too. Want to join us?</i>

646
00:39:25,029 --> 00:39:26,664
- I'll be off.
- Bye.

647
00:39:27,932 --> 00:39:30,234
- Do you come this way often?
- Yes, I do.

648
00:39:30,301 --> 00:39:32,370
Were you here two weeks ago
on a Saturday night

649
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:34,672
at around 10:00 p.m.?

650
00:39:35,639 --> 00:39:37,675
- I always pass by here.
- Is that right?

651
00:39:37,742 --> 00:39:41,245
Do you remember if the light was on
at this hair salon?

652
00:39:41,812 --> 00:39:44,014
I don't remember that.

653
00:39:44,081 --> 00:39:45,850
I don't think I was paying attention.

654
00:39:47,918 --> 00:39:49,520
The light was on.

655
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:51,589
You're sure?

656
00:39:52,623 --> 00:39:54,358
Since I'm a hair stylist,

657
00:39:54,959 --> 00:39:58,596
when I see a salon with the lights on,
I tend to wonder if they're practicing.

658
00:39:59,430 --> 00:40:00,765
- So it catches my eye.
- I see.

659
00:40:00,831 --> 00:40:03,300
Did you happen to see who was inside?

660
00:40:04,068 --> 00:40:06,203
I did see a figure inside.

661
00:40:08,472 --> 00:40:10,508
<i>It was a woman, right?</i>

662
00:40:10,574 --> 00:40:14,378
Well, the manager of this place
is a woman, right?

663
00:40:14,445 --> 00:40:15,980
Yes, that's right.

664
00:40:25,723 --> 00:40:26,857
This is Nara.

665
00:40:27,825 --> 00:40:28,726
This is Tobina.

666
00:40:29,293 --> 00:40:31,028
<i>What is it, Detective Tobina?</i>

667
00:40:31,095 --> 00:40:32,897
You're off duty today, right?

668
00:40:33,964 --> 00:40:37,435
Regarding Ms. Makiko Iwamoto's alibi,

669
00:40:37,501 --> 00:40:41,806
I got two testimonies stating that
the lights were on in the hair salon

670
00:40:41,872 --> 00:40:45,810
and that there was a person inside
around 10:00 p.m. on Saturday night.

671
00:40:45,876 --> 00:40:47,878
That's wonderful.

672
00:40:48,412 --> 00:40:50,147
Then good day.

673
00:40:59,256 --> 00:41:00,257
Um…

674
00:41:00,758 --> 00:41:03,561
Isn't it best to tell your buddy Tobina
about this…?

675
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:10,701
<i>No way, no way.</i>

676
00:41:10,768 --> 00:41:11,936
- No.
- You did it five times.

677
00:41:12,002 --> 00:41:12,837
No, I didn't.

678
00:41:12,903 --> 00:41:14,472
Naoto, you should drink too.

679
00:41:14,538 --> 00:41:16,073
But I drove here.

680
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:17,608
I drove here too.

681
00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:19,243
He can stay the night, right?

682
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:21,278
Yeah. Just sleep over there.

683
00:41:23,881 --> 00:41:25,115
I got a message from Junichi.

684
00:41:25,182 --> 00:41:26,250
What did he say?

685
00:41:26,317 --> 00:41:27,184
He said he's coming.

686
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:29,119
Really?

687
00:41:32,723 --> 00:41:33,624
Is that him?

688
00:41:40,097 --> 00:41:41,098
What?

689
00:41:42,099 --> 00:41:43,000
Detectives.

690
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,401
Good evening.

691
00:41:45,202 --> 00:41:46,403
What brings you here?

692
00:41:47,571 --> 00:41:48,639
Naoto.

693
00:41:51,842 --> 00:41:53,544
You're all here.

694
00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:57,381
We meet again, just as I promised.

695
00:41:58,415 --> 00:41:59,917
Sorry for coming this late.

696
00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:02,453
Yes, this is absurd.

697
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,388
Ms. Iwamoto has a young child too.

698
00:42:05,322 --> 00:42:07,558
Would you mind accompanying me
to the police station…

699
00:42:12,796 --> 00:42:14,298
Mr. Naoto Sakuma.

700
00:42:15,499 --> 00:42:16,333
What?

701
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:18,769
There is something I'd like to ask you.

702
00:42:19,436 --> 00:42:21,171
What's going on?

703
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:25,543
It doesn't take an hour to get
to your house from Haneda, right?

704
00:42:27,144 --> 00:42:32,049
Is it true that you were caught
in a traffic jam that day?

705
00:42:32,616 --> 00:42:34,184
I didn't get home until

706
00:42:35,185 --> 00:42:37,588
a little before 11:00 p.m.

707
00:42:37,655 --> 00:42:38,989
<i>Our investigation</i>

708
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:42,326
had quickly revealed that there was
no traffic congestion on either

709
00:42:42,393 --> 00:42:43,861
the highway or the local roads.

710
00:42:44,528 --> 00:42:45,563
So

711
00:42:46,797 --> 00:42:50,234
I'd been searching for sightings
of your car that evening.

712
00:42:53,170 --> 00:42:54,438
Then lo and behold,

713
00:42:54,939 --> 00:42:57,074
on Saturday, the day of the murder,

714
00:42:58,242 --> 00:43:00,844
you and your car were captured

715
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:05,249
on the security camera at a gas station.

716
00:43:06,617 --> 00:43:08,185
It was 10:05 p.m.,

717
00:43:08,686 --> 00:43:11,221
as evidenced by the gas station's records.

718
00:43:12,523 --> 00:43:16,594
It is about a ten minute drive
from the crime scene, Smile Sakuma.

719
00:43:17,661 --> 00:43:18,562
In other words,

720
00:43:19,363 --> 00:43:23,968
it means you could have been present
at the scene of the murder.

721
00:43:26,537 --> 00:43:27,538
Naoto.

722
00:43:42,152 --> 00:43:43,287
Nagai.

723
00:43:43,354 --> 00:43:44,989
- What's going on?
- Mr. Tobina.

724
00:43:46,991 --> 00:43:48,659
What are you doing, Ms. Nara?

725
00:43:51,295 --> 00:43:52,696
His alibi has fallen apart.

726
00:43:53,864 --> 00:43:56,600
Mr. Naoto Sakuma will
voluntarily accompany us to the station.

727
00:44:12,750 --> 00:44:13,550
IS HIS FORMER CLASSMATE
REALLY THE CULPRIT?

728
00:44:13,617 --> 00:44:14,918
I killed my older brother.

729
00:44:14,985 --> 00:44:18,088
I think he always had feelings for Makiko.

730
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:19,957
<i>Please come right now, Junichi.</i>

731
00:44:20,024 --> 00:44:23,694
<i>If one of us is lying,</i>
<i>who will you believe?</i>

732
00:44:23,761 --> 00:44:26,196
I thought you would never come back.

733
00:44:26,263 --> 00:44:27,698
I saw it.

734
00:44:27,765 --> 00:44:28,666
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
